dataset.title: School District Boundaries
dataset.description: This layer contains school district boundary polygons and related attributes.  This layer is compiled by using the Auditor's annexation layer and is updated as new annexations are processed by the office.

dataset.title: Historical Townships
dataset.description: This dataset contains municipal, school and other related administrative or jurisdictional boundaries in the ESRI Local Government Information Model format.  Additional feature datasets have been added and include; Historic Districts; Historic Townships; Zip Codes.  Data schemas have been adjusted to meet FCA requierments.

dataset.title: 1995 Aerial Photography
dataset.description: 1995 Ortho Aerial Photography of Franklin County and Surrounding Areas.

dataset.title: Parcel CSV Files
dataset.description: These CSV files contains fields detailing property, tax, and value data maintained by various divisions within the Auditor's office. Documentation can be found in the documentation folder on the FTP site.  This data is provided from 1997-Present and is generally produced on a quarterly basis.

dataset.title: 2011 Contour Elevations
dataset.description: This layer contains elevation contours derived from 2011 OSIP LiDAR Collection.  Twenty, Ten, Five, and Two foot contour intervals are available at various mapping scales for Franklin County and the entire City of Columbus.

dataset.title: Municipal Boundaries
dataset.description: This layer contains municipal boundary polygons and related attributes.  This layer is compiled by using the Auditor's annexation layer and is updated as new annexations are processed by the office.

dataset.title: County Boundaries
dataset.description: This layer contains county boundary polygons and related attributes for Franklin and surrounding counties.

dataset.title: 2000 Aerial Photography
dataset.description: 2000 Ortho Aerial Photography of Franklin County and Surrounding Areas.

dataset.title: Special Tax Districts
dataset.description: This layer contains special tax district boundaries and related attributes for TIFs, SIDs, CRAs, and other special taxing districts. These areas are generally defined by municipal governments but managed by the Auditor's office because of their impact on taxes.

dataset.title: UAV Flight Paths
dataset.description: This layer contains the flight paths of UAV surveys that were flown in 2018. According to the necessary survey, data is depicted as either a line or a polygon.

dataset.title: UAV Visual Extents
dataset.description: This layer contains boundaries and related attribute information of the approximate visual extents of individual UAV flights. Visual extents may overlap multiple parcels.

dataset.title: Appraisal Neighborhood Boundaries
dataset.description: This layer contains appraisal neighborhood boundaries and related attributes within Franklin County. Appraisal Neighborhoods are defined by the appraisal department.

dataset.title: Railroads
dataset.description: This layer contains line features of railroads (active and inactive).  This layer is derived from a number of sources including compilation from aerial photography and is part of the planimetric (base map) mapping conducted by the Auditor's office.

dataset.title: Parcel Points (Centroids)
dataset.description: This layer contains parcel centroids and related attributes for parcels within Franklin County.  Condominium units are depicted as individual units and are spatially correct. For other attribute schema see our direct download site.

dataset.title: Outside User Files
dataset.description: These CSV files contains fields detailing property, tax, and value data maintained by various divisions within the Auditor's office and are more comprehensive than the parcel CSV file.  Documentation can be found in each folder on the FTP site.  This data is provided from 2014 to present and is generally produced on a quarterly basis.

dataset.title: UAV Flights
dataset.description: This map depicts UAV Flights that were conducted for Franklin County Auditor in 2018.

dataset.description: This layer contains polygon features of water bodies large enough to identify on 6-inch aerial photography.  This layer was originally derived from the 2011 OSIP LiDAR collection but is updated as part of the planimetric (base map) mapping conducted by the Auditor's office.

dataset.description: This layer contains UAV survey origin locations and attribute data associated with those locations. Locations are depicted as individual points. This data also includes the URL of the UAV imagery captured in 2018.

dataset.title: Creeks & Streams
dataset.description: This layer contains line features of water and drainage not large enough to map in polygon form.  This layer was originally derived from the 2011 OSIP LiDAR collection but is updated as part of the planimetric (base map) mapping conducted by the Auditor's office.

dataset.title: Annexations
dataset.description: This layer contains polygons showing annexations. It is updated as new annexations are processed by the office.

dataset.title: Street Centerlines
dataset.description: This street centerline layer contains attributes for address ranges. A cooperative agreement among local agencies within Franklin County allows entities to maintain one common road centerline file. The original file contains a six mile buffer outside of Franklin County in order to provide complete coverage to cities that extend outside of the county boundary. This service is limited to Franklin County only. The Franklin County portion of the file is part of the ODOT/OGRIP statewide LBRS program and is periodically incorporated into their system.

dataset.title: Edge of Pavement
dataset.description: This layer contains line features representing the edge of pavement.  This layer was originally derived from the 2011 OSIP LiDAR collection but is updated as part of the planimetric (base map) mapping conducted by the Auditor's office.

dataset.title: Registered Rental Properties
dataset.description: This point layer contains properties that are registered with the Franklin County Auditor as rental properties. This is not an exhaustive list of rental properties,however it is all properties that are have an active rental registration on file with the Auditor's office. This layer is regenerated weekly.  The parcel centroid values are utilized to create these points with condominium units being spatially accurate.

dataset.title: Building Footprints
dataset.description: This layer contains polygon features of buildings and other similar structures.  This layer was developed and is maintained as part of the planimetric (base map) mapping conducted by the Auditor's office.

dataset.title: Property Foreclosures
dataset.description: This point layer contains Property Transaction where a Sheriffs Deed (SH or SX) was filed as the latest instrument. This data is regenerated nightly based on the previous day's transactions. Only the latest instrument is utilized in the creation of this layer. The parcel centroid values are utilized to create these points with condominium units being spatially accurate.

dataset.title: Board of Revision Cases
dataset.description: This point layer contains properties that have an active Board of Revision Case filing since 2016. This layer is regenerated nightly based on the previous days' transactions and case status is updated regularly.  The parcel centroid values are utilized to create these points with condominium units being spatially accurate.

dataset.title: Property Sales Transactions
dataset.description: This point layer contains Property Sales Transaction by Land Use Type for the years 2017 through present.  This layer is regenerated nightly based on the previous day's transactions and symbolized by year of sale. The parcel centroid values are utilized to create these points with condominium units being spatially accurate.

dataset.title: Tax Delinquent Properties
dataset.description: This point layer contains properties where that are actively in a tax delinquent status. This layer is regenerated nightly, based on the previous day's transactions. The parcel centroid values are utilized to create these points with condominium units being spatially accurate.

dataset.title: Parcel Boundaries
dataset.description: This layer contains parcel boundaries and related attributes for parcels within Franklin County, Ohio.  Condominium units are depicted as individual parcels.  Condominium Common Areas are identified with a polygon and simple attribute found in the Parcel ID field.  For other attribute schema and geometry types please see our direct download site.

dataset.title: Subdivision & Condominium Boundaries
dataset.description: This layer contains subdivision and condominium boundaries and related attributes within Franklin County. Common and legal name attributes are provided for each polygon and these conform to parcel boundaries and right-of-way layers.
